g.title: Parser must call advance() within skip loops to maintain line/col sync

ol.li: self.line is incremented exclusively within advance() when char == '\n'.
self.column resets to 1 on \n, else increments via self.column += 1.
Token objects capture line and column snapshots from self.line and self.start_column.

g.text: python # Internal State (Byte Offsets for 64-bit CPython) 0x00 | str | source # Ptr to input buffer 0x08 | int | start # Lexeme start index 0x10 | int | current # Current cursor pos 0x18 | int | line # 1-based line counter 0x20 | int | column # 1-based column counter 0x28 | int | start_column # Column at lexeme start
